(58, 1, 1, 42, 24, 27, 27, 'by the prophets', 'Connection of Prophetic Revelation', 'This connection highlights how God spoke through the prophets, as noted in Hebrews, and how Jesus expounded on these prophetic scriptures in Luke. Both passages emphasize the continuity of God''s revelation through the prophets.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 1, 60, 1, 10, 12, 'spake in time past unto the fathers by the prophets', 'Connection of Prophetic Revelation', 'This connection highlights the role of prophets in conveying God''s message. Both passages emphasize how the prophets spoke and searched for understanding regarding the future grace and sufferings of Christ.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 1, 1, 46, 2, 4, 'spake in time past unto the fathers', 'Divine Communication to the Patriarchs', 'This connection highlights how God communicates directly with His chosen leaders. Both passages emphasize God''s initiative in speaking to His people, guiding them in significant moments of their lives.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 1, 42, 1, 55, 55, NULL, 'Connection of God''s Communication', 'This connection highlights God''s communication to the fathers through the prophets in Hebrews and references to the fathers in Luke. Both passages emphasize the continuity of God''s promises to Abraham and his descendants.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 2, 43, 1, 3, 3, 'by whom also he made the worlds', 'Creation Through the Son', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the Son in creation. Hebrews states that all things were made by him, which parallels John''s assertion that without him was not any thing made that was made.', 'theme', 0.552, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 2, 46, 8, 6, 6, 'by whom also he made the worlds', 'Connection of Divine Agency', 'Both passages emphasize the role of Jesus Christ as the agent through whom all things are made. Hebrews highlights that God spoke through His Son, while 1 Corinthians affirms that all things are by Him.', 'theme', 0.5309999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 2, 51, 1, 16, 18, 'by whom also he made the worlds', 'Creation and Preeminence of Christ', 'Both passages emphasize that all things were created by Christ, highlighting his role as the agent of creation and his preeminence over all creation. Hebrews states he made the worlds, while Colossians elaborates on his authority over all things.', 'theme', 0.524, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 2, 43, 1, 14, 14, 'by whom also he made the worlds', 'Connection of the Word and Son', 'This connection highlights the role of the Son as the agent of creation and revelation. Both passages emphasize the divine nature of the Son, with Hebrews referring to Him as the one by whom the worlds were made, and John identifying Him as the Word made flesh.', 'theme', 0.489, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 2, 60, 1, 20, 20, 'these last days', 'Connection of Last Days and Foreordination', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''these last days'' and the foreordained nature of the Son. This connection highlights the significance of Jesus'' role in God''s plan from the foundation of the world.', 'theme', 0.482, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 2, 40, 28, 18, 18, 'whom he hath appointed heir of all things', 'Authority of Jesus Christ', 'This connection highlights the authority of Jesus as both the appointed heir and the one given all power in heaven and earth. Both passages emphasize the significance of Jesus'' role in relation to creation and authority.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 2, 50, 2, 9, 11, 'appointed heir of all things', 'Exaltation of Jesus Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the authority and exaltation of Jesus. Hebrews highlights Jesus as the appointed heir of all things, while Philippians declares that every knee should bow to Him, affirming His supreme status.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 3, 51, 1, 15, 17, 'the express image of his person', 'Connection of Christ''s Image', 'Both passages emphasize Christ as the ''image'' of God, highlighting his divine nature and role in creation. Hebrews describes him as the ''express image of his person,'' while Colossians refers to him as ''the image of the invisible God.''', 'theme', 0.776, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 3, 66, 4, 11, 11, 'the brightness of his glory', 'Divine Glory and Creation', 'This connection highlights the shared theme of divine glory and power. Both passages emphasize the worthiness of the Lord in relation to creation and the sustaining of all things.', 'theme', 0.566, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 3, 43, 14, 9, 10, 'express image of his person', 'Connection of Divine Presence', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between Jesus and the Father, highlighting that seeing Jesus is akin to seeing God. Hebrews describes Jesus as the ''express image'' of God, while John asserts that knowing Jesus is knowing the Father.', 'theme', 0.475, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 3, 43, 1, 14, 14, 'the brightness of his glory', 'Connection of Glory and Word', 'This connection highlights the theme of glory, as both passages refer to the divine glory of Jesus. Hebrews describes Him as ''the brightness of his glory,'' while John states that ''we beheld his glory.''', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 3, 47, 4, 4, 4, 'the express image of his person', 'Connection of Divine Image and Light', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being the ''image of God'' and the ''brightness of his glory.'' This connection highlights the role of Christ as the manifestation of divine light and glory, revealing God''s nature to humanity.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 3, 58, 12, 2, 2, 'sat down on the right hand', 'Connection of Jesus'' Authority', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' position at the right hand of God, highlighting his authority and role in salvation. The first passage describes him as having purged our sins and sitting down, while the second focuses on him as the author and finisher of faith, also seated at God''s right hand.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 3, 58, 10, 12, 12, 'sat down on the right hand', 'Connection of Christ''s Sacrifice', 'Both passages emphasize the act of Christ sitting down on the right hand of God after offering a sacrifice for sins. This connection highlights the completion of His redemptive work and His exalted position.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 4, 49, 1, 21, 21, 'more excellent name than they', 'Connection of Superiority', 'Both passages emphasize the superiority of Christ over all spiritual beings and authorities. Hebrews highlights His more excellent name than angels, while Ephesians states He is far above all principality and power.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 4, 50, 2, 9, 11, 'a more excellent name than they', 'Exaltation and Name of Jesus', 'This connection highlights the theme of Jesus'' exaltation and the significance of His name. Both passages emphasize that Jesus has obtained a name that is superior, with Hebrews noting His more excellent name and Philippians declaring it as above every name.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 4, 60, 3, 22, 22, 'better than the angels', 'Authority Over Angels', 'Both passages emphasize the superiority of Christ over angels. Hebrews 1:4 states that Christ is ''made so much better than the angels,'' while 1 Peter 3:22 notes that angels are made subject to Him.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
