(58, 1, 4, 66, 5, 11, 12, 'better than the angels', 'Angelic Worship of the Lamb', 'Both passages emphasize the superiority of Christ over angels. Hebrews highlights His more excellent name, while Revelation depicts angels proclaiming the worthiness of the Lamb. This connection highlights the recognition of Christ''s divine authority.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 4, 19, 2, 7, 8, 'inheritance obtained a more excellent name', 'Connection of Sonship and Inheritance', 'This connection highlights the theme of inheritance and sonship. Hebrews 1:4 speaks of Jesus obtaining a more excellent name through inheritance, while Psalms 2:7-8 declares Him as God''s Son and mentions inheritance of the nations.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 4, 53, 1, 7, 7, 'better than the angels', 'Connection of Jesus and Angels', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between Jesus and angels. Hebrews highlights Jesus'' superiority over angels, while 2 Thessalonians mentions his revelation with mighty angels.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 5, 19, 2, 7, 7, 'Thou art my Son', 'Connection of Sonship', 'Both passages emphasize the declaration of sonship, with the phrase ''Thou art my Son'' appearing in both. Hebrews 1:5 directly quotes Psalms 2:7, linking the two texts through this shared declaration.', 'quotation', 0.7689999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 5, 44, 13, 33, 33, 'Thou art my Son, this day have I begotten thee', 'Connection of Sonship in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the phrase, ''Thou art my Son, this day have I begotten thee,'' linking the concept of Jesus'' divine sonship. Hebrews 1:5 discusses the unique relationship between God and Jesus, while Acts 13:33 affirms the fulfillment of this declaration through Jesus'' resurrection.', 'quotation', 0.594, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 5, 58, 5, 5, 5, 'Thou art my Son', 'Connection of Sonship and Priesthood', 'Both passages emphasize the declaration of Christ as God''s Son. The phrase ''Thou art my Son'' links the identity of Christ in both contexts, highlighting his divine sonship and role as high priest.', 'quotation', 0.5309999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 5, 10, 7, 14, 14, 'I will be to him a Father, and he shall be to me a Son', 'Father-Son Relationship', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship of father and son, with Hebrews quoting the declaration of sonship and 2 Samuel affirming God''s paternal role. This connection highlights the continuity of divine sonship across the texts.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 5, 13, 17, 13, 13, 'I will be to him a Father, and he shall be to me a Son', 'Father-Son Relationship', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between God as Father and the figure identified as His Son. Hebrews 1:5 directly quotes the concept of God declaring, ''I will be to him a Father, and he shall be to me a Son,'' which parallels the declaration in 1 Chronicles 17:13.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 5, 13, 22, 10, 10, 'I will be to him a Father, and he shall be to me a Son', 'Father-Son Relationship Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship of a father and son, with God declaring, ''I will be his father; and he shall be my son.'' This connection highlights the significance of divine sonship in the context of leadership and authority.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 5, 19, 89, 26, 27, 'Thou art my Son, this day have I begotten thee', 'Connection of Sonship and Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship of sonship between God and the anointed one. Hebrews quotes the declaration of being a Son, while Psalms refers to making him my firstborn, indicating a position of authority.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 6, 19, 97, 7, 7, NULL, 'Worship of the Divine', 'This connection highlights the theme of worship directed towards the divine. Both passages emphasize the command to worship, with Hebrews calling for angels to worship the firstbegotten and Psalms urging all gods to worship Him.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
