(58, 1, 6, 5, 32, 43, 43, 'let all the angels of God worship him', 'Worship and Vengeance Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine authority and the response of creation. In Hebrews, the angels are called to worship the firstbegotten, while in Deuteronomy, nations are called to rejoice with God''s people, emphasizing God''s sovereignty and the reverence due to Him.', 'theme', 0.426, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 6, 60, 3, 22, 22, 'let all the angels of God worship him', 'Worship and Authority of Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of Christ''s supremacy over angels. Both passages emphasize the worship of Christ by angels and His authority over them.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 6, 43, 1, 14, 14, 'firstbegotten', 'Worship and Begotten Connection', 'This connection highlights the concept of the ''firstbegotten'' and ''only begotten,'' emphasizing the unique status of Jesus. Both passages affirm His divine nature and the reverence due to Him, as seen in the worship of angels.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 6, 66, 5, 9, 12, 'let all the angels of God worship him', 'Worship of the Lamb', 'Both passages emphasize the worship of Jesus as the firstbegotten and the Lamb that was slain. Hebrews highlights the angels worshiping Him, while Revelation depicts a multitude praising His worthiness.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 6, 66, 1, 5, 5, 'firstbegotten', 'Connection of First Begotten', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus as the ''first begotten,'' linking his divine status and resurrection. Hebrews highlights his worship by angels, while Revelation identifies him as the ''first begotten of the dead.''', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
