(58, 1, 8, 24, 23, 5, 6, 'a sceptre of righteousness is the sceptre of thy kingdom', 'Connection of Righteous Kingship', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of a righteous king who reigns forever. Hebrews 1:8 refers to the Son''s eternal throne, while Jeremiah 23:5-6 speaks of a righteous Branch from David who will execute justice.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 8, 45, 9, 5, 5, 'O God, is for ever and ever', 'Divine Authority of Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the divine nature of Christ, referring to Him as ''God'' and highlighting His eternal reign. Hebrews 1:8 declares the Son''s throne as everlasting, while Romans 9:5 affirms Christ''s supremacy over all.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 8, 43, 10, 30, 30, 'Thy throne, O God, is for ever', 'Divine Authority and Unity', 'This connection highlights the divine authority of the Son, as seen in Hebrews where He is addressed as God with an eternal throne. Similarly, in John, the statement ''I and my Father are one'' emphasizes the unity and shared authority between the Son and the Father.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 8, 62, 5, 20, 20, 'Thy throne, O God, is for ever', 'Connection of Divine Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the divine nature of the Son. Hebrews 1:8 refers to the Son as God with an eternal throne, while 1 John 5:20 identifies Jesus Christ as the true God and eternal life.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 8, 23, 7, 14, 14, 'Thy throne, O God, is for ever', 'Connection of Divine Sonship', 'This connection highlights the divine nature of the Son in Hebrews, paralleling the prophetic announcement of Immanuel in Isaiah. Both passages emphasize the significance of a son who embodies God''s authority and presence.', 'theme', 0.377, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
