(58, 1, 9, 23, 61, 3, 3, 'the oil of gladness', 'Connection of Righteousness and Joy', 'This connection highlights the theme of righteousness and joy in both passages. Hebrews 1:9 mentions ''the oil of gladness,'' while Isaiah 61:3 refers to ''the oil of joy,'' linking the concepts of divine anointing and joy in the context of righteousness.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 9, 48, 5, 22, 22, 'oil of gladness', 'Connection of Righteousness and Joy', 'This connection highlights the theme of righteousness leading to joy. Hebrews 1:9 mentions ''the oil of gladness,'' which parallels the ''joy'' found in the fruit of the Spirit in Galatians 5:22.', 'theme', 0.37, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 9, 45, 15, 13, 13, 'oil of gladness', 'Connection of Joy and Righteousness', 'This connection highlights the theme of joy linked to righteousness. Both passages emphasize the importance of righteousness and the resulting joy and peace that comes from God.', 'theme', 0.356, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 9, 30, 5, 15, 15, 'loved righteousness, and hated iniquity', 'Connection of Righteousness and Evil', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of loving righteousness and hating iniquity or evil. This connection highlights a moral imperative that aligns with God''s expectations for His people.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 9, 42, 4, 18, 18, 'anointed thee with the oil of gladness', 'Connection of Anointing and Mission', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of anointing for a divine purpose. Hebrews 1:9 speaks of being anointed with the oil of gladness, while Luke 4:18 describes the anointing to preach and heal. This connection highlights the role of the anointed in fulfilling God''s mission.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 10, 19, 102, 25, 27, 'foundation of the earth', 'Creation and Endurance of the Earth', 'Both passages emphasize the foundation of the earth as the work of God''s hands. They also highlight the contrast between the perishable nature of creation and God''s eternal existence.', 'theme', 0.566, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
