(58, 1, 10, 43, 1, 1, 3, 'foundation of the earth', 'Creation and Divine Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the act of creation, attributing the foundation of the earth and the heavens to God. Hebrews 1:10 speaks of God laying the foundation, while John 1:3 states that all things were made by the Word, which is identified with God.', 'theme', 0.46799999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 10, 24, 32, 17, 17, NULL, 'Creation by God''s Power', 'Both passages emphasize God''s role as the creator of heaven and earth, highlighting His great power in establishing the foundations of creation. This connection underscores the divine authority and capability attributed to God in both texts.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 10, 19, 8, 3, 4, 'the heavens are the works of thine hands', 'Creation and Humanity''s Place', 'Both passages emphasize the creation of the heavens and earth, highlighting God''s role as the creator. They also reflect on humanity''s significance in relation to this vast creation.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(58, 1, 10, 23, 48, 13, 13, 'laid the foundation of the earth', 'Creation and Divine Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the act of laying the foundation of the earth, highlighting God''s creative authority. The use of ''laid the foundation of the earth'' in both texts connects them thematically.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
